OL,3,CProposition to remove Jersey Bailiff
OL,4,Cfrom States Assembly withdrawn
OL,6,FIf approved, the Bailiff would still
OL,7,Fpreside in the Assembly on Liberation
OL,8,FDay, on a Royal Visit, and be invited
OL,9,Fto preside in or address the Assembly
OL,10,Fon other ceremonial or appropriate
OL,11,Foccasions.
OL,13,FIt follows Jersey's Bailiff, Sir
OL,14,FTimothy Le Cocq, announcing his
OL,15,Fretirement from office in October.
OL,17,FHe explains: "I have been of the view
OL,18,Ffor many years that, whilst it is
OL,19,Fimportant to respect our traditions,
OL,20,FJersey must always seek to meet key
OL,21,Fdemocratic principles.
